wiki.text:
'Factor XI' or 'plasma thromboplastin antecedent' is the zymogen form of factor
XIa, one of the enzymes of the coagulation cascade. Like many other coagulation
factors, it is a serine protease. In humans, Factor XI is encoded by the F11
gene.<ref name="pmid3636155"></ref><ref name="pmid2827746"></ref><ref
name="pmid2612218"></ref><ref name="pmid1673289"></ref>
